name: Vintage Banjara Fabric Clutch 9
description:
Each of these unique clutches is hand constructed from vintage Indian fabrics.

Originating from the hill tribes of India, the Banjara women are renowned for their colourful and beautiful saris adorned with mirror chips and silver coins for decoration.

With an eye for detail, the patchwork of colours and textures are sewn into an envelope shape clutch that holds its shape and tucks perfectly under the arm.

These gorgeous bags are a versatile everyday accessory.

Fabric - cotton
Size - 36cm x 18cm approx
Internal features - cotton lined with zip pocket for phone or valuables
